Paper: hep-th/9401027

Date: 1994-01-07

Title: Higher-Dimensional Loop Algebras, Non-Abelian Extensions and p-Branes

Authors: M. Cederwall, G. Ferretti, B.E.W. Nilsson and A. Westerberg

Comments: (published version, extended introduction), 35 pp.(LaTeX), Goteborg

ITP-93-37Journal-ref: Nucl.Phys. B424 (1994) 97-123

We postulate a new type of operator algebra with a non-abelian extension.This algebra generalizes the Kac--Moody algebra in string theory and theMickelsson--Faddeev algebra in three dimensions to higher-dimensional extendedobjects ($p$-branes). We then construct new BRST operators, covariantderivatives and curvature tensors in the higher-dimensional generalization ofloop space.